The paper deals with the development of an onboard target detection, tracking and avoidance system for low-cost UAV flight controllers using AI-based approaches. Therefore, the most likely category is Robotics (cs.RO) as it involves UAVs and their control. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also likely as the paper uses a state-of-the-art object detection technique called SSD. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category as the paper uses AI-based approaches for target detection and tracking. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques for target detection and tracking. Finally, Systems and Control (cs.SY) is another possible category as the paper deals with the control of UAVs for target avoidance.
